.TH UTILITYKIT 1 "July 2026" "UtilityKit v5.10.6" "UtilityKit Tools"
.SH NAME
utility-docker_janitor \- Preview and prune stopped containers, dangling images, and orphaned volumes from a local Docker installation. Shows a disk usage summary before any action is taken.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B utility docker_janitor
[\fIoptions\fP]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Preview and prune stopped containers, dangling images, and orphaned volumes from a local Docker installation. Shows a disk usage summary before any action is taken.
.SH FEATURES
.PP
.IP \(bu 4
\fBContainer pruning\fP — removes exited and stopped containers
.IP \(bu 4
\fBImage pruning\fP — removes dangling untagged image layers
.IP \(bu 4
\fBVolume pruning\fP — removes volumes no longer attached to any container
.IP \(bu 4
\fBDisk usage summary\fP — displays \fCdocker system df\fP output before prompting
.IP \(bu 4
\fBSafe by default\fP — nothing is deleted until you explicitly confirm with \fC--apply\fP
.IP \(bu 4
\fBInteractive mode\fP — running without arguments shows counts and prompts for each category
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH USAGE
.PP
.EX
bash _docker_janitor/_docker_janitor.sh

bash _docker_janitor/_docker_janitor.sh --containers --images

bash _docker_janitor/_docker_janitor.sh --containers --apply

bash _docker_janitor/_docker_janitor.sh --images --apply

bash _docker_janitor/_docker_janitor.sh --all --apply
.EE
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
Option   |   Description
\fC--containers\fP   |   Select stopped containers for pruning
\fC--images\fP   |   Select dangling images for pruning
\fC--volumes\fP   |   Select dangling volumes for pruning
\fC--all\fP   |   Select all three categories at once
\fC--apply\fP   |   Execute the selected prune operations
\fC-h, --help\fP   |   Show usage
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH WHAT EACH CATEGORY REMOVES
.PP
Category   |   What is removed   |   What is kept
Containers   |   Exited and stopped containers   |   Running containers, images, volumes
Images   |   Untagged dangling image layers   |   Named and tagged images
Volumes   |   Volumes with no container reference   |   Volumes attached to any container
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH PREVIEW OUTPUT
.PP
Before any prompts the tool always displays current counts and disk usage:
.PP
.EX
  Stopped containers   3   (exited and no longer running)
  Dangling images      7   (untagged layers with no active reference)
  Dangling volumes     2   (volumes no longer attached to any container)

  Disk usage summary:
  TYPE            TOTAL     ACTIVE    SIZE      RECLAIMABLE
  Images          12        5         2.1GB     890MB (42%)
  Containers      3         0         0B        0B
  Local Volumes   4         2         512MB     210MB (41%)
.EE
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH NOTES
.PP
.IP \(bu 4
Volume pruning is the most destructive option — data stored inside orphaned volumes is permanently lost
.IP \(bu 4
This tool is not useful inside Termux since Docker is generally unavailable on Android
.IP \(bu 4
The tool verifies that the Docker daemon is reachable before doing anything
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH EXIT CODES
.PP
Code   |   Meaning
\fC0\fP   |   Success
\fC1\fP   |   Docker not found or daemon not reachable
